Author: ARround Team
Title: ARROUND: breakthrough advertising and communication platform in AR
Body: There were rumors recently that Apple had closed the project for the development of an AR headset. And as if in denial of these conjectures, the company received another patent for technology for a mixed reality device. The upcoming headset can include several sensors to track eyes, gestures, and even facial expressions of users. The patent application entitled ‚ÄúDisplay System Having Sensors‚Äù was first filed in March of this year and published last week. Apple has already developed face tracking software for animated AR emoji. Apple has been working on its own AR / MR headset for several years. At first it was thought that it would be just compact AR glasses. However, Apple has not officially commented on its plans for the headset.

Author: ARround Team
Title: ARROUND: breakthrough advertising and communication platform in AR
Body: Google has published a major update of the translation of augmented reality in the Google Translate application for Android and iOS. The new version has support for 60 new languages, the function is less sharp (more natural) text visualization; New basic translation models, in some cases capable of reducing the number of errors by 85%. This is a solution to the main known application problems.  The key to the update was the integration of translation methods using artificial intelligence, known as neural machine translation. He is already working in Google Lens and the web version of the Translator.  The latest version of the application also automatically detects the language that the camera sees. This is useful if you are traveling in a region where several languages are spoken.  The global release of the update will take place within a few weeks.

Author: ARround Team
Title: ARROUND: breakthrough advertising and communication platform in AR
Body: ARROUND successfully completed the All-Russian 3D-modeling competition for schoolchildren and students "Co3Datel" which we were holding Together with CODDY and the School of New Technologies, with the support of the Moscow Department of Education and the Department of Information Technologies, we completed the ‚ÄúCo3Datel‚Äù contest, the final of which was held at the VDNH in Moscow on April 13. Our main goal is to promote exitement in the field of science and technology, to help young people develop their talents in the field of IT, in particular, in the field of software development for augmented reality, which has shown significant growth over the past few years. The jury included such prominent figures of the IT market as Oksana Selendeeva (founder of the programming school ‚ÄúCODDY‚Äù), Temur Shakaya and Evgeny Dobrovolsky (co-founders of ARROUND). Firstly, they had to evaluate the work using the application of augmented reality. The winners received valuable prizes. So, Niyaz Divayev, who made the project ‚ÄúMobile Manipulator on Omni Wheels‚Äù, will go on a tour of the MiG production factory, Alexander Germ, who virtualized the picture of Salvador Dali, won a trip to Tokyo, Nikolai Sikovoy, who created a highly detailed animated model of a man, got a computer 3D-modeler, and Alexey Girich, with the project ‚ÄúTakhion 9980XE‚Äù - the opportunity to have an internship at ARROUND. The competition was brilliant and everyone was delighted, so ARROUND and the rest of the organizers decided to hold it on the future bases. Stay with us and follow the news. Let's build a new universe together!

Title: ARROUND: breakthrough advertising and communication platform in AR
Body: On February 18, we launched the first All-Russian 3D modeling competition for schoolchildren and university students ‚Äî CO–óDATE–õ–¨ (CREATOR).  The ARROUND team and our partners set the goal of identifying and encouraging talented young people who are interested in 3D modeling, as well as helping them to find innovative solutions at the intersection of art and high technology. Schoolchildren and students from all over Russia can practically show their abilities in creating artistic and technological projects for augmented reality ‚Äî and will be appreciated by real experts from the industry!  Who is the organizer?  We are the augmented reality platform ARROUND, together with the CODDY International Programming School with the support of the Russia's Moscow Department of Information Technologies, Moscow Department of Education, School of New Technologies project, Moscow Institute for Technological Modernization of Education, the Institute of Business Administration of the RANEPA, and Soyuzmultfilm Studios. Partners include Coca-Cola, Colin‚Äôs, FSUE NAMI, and Sollers.  How does the competition go?  It consists of two stages. Until March 18, experts will evaluate the uploaded works, forming a list of those who went to the on-site stage. On April 13, at the Exhibition of Economic Achievements, participants will present their projects on platform ARROUND to the experts.  How to participate?  It‚Äôs very simple, just register on the site: https://3d.coddyschool.com  Is it free?  Absolutely. Moreover, all participants will receive valuable prizes.  What are the prizes?  The prizes of the competition are: a computer of a 3D modeler, a trip to St. Petersburg, an internship at ARROUND and Soyuzmultfilm Studios, a visit to FSUE NAMI (where the procession of A Cortege and Aurus is being developed). The main prize is provided by the chairman of the jury E.Y. Dobrovolsky, and it‚Äôs a trip to Tokyo.   If you have always wanted to create something that has never happened before, change the reality with your creativity and with the help of technology ‚Äî this competition is created especially for you. Author: LordAltcoin
Title: ARROUND: breakthrough advertising and communication platform in AR
Body: UPDATE:  I was able to send the ARR tokens from Wallet to MEW (My Ether Wallet) This is how its done.  Log into MEW  1 - Add Smart Contract Address for Arround.  https://etherscan.io/token/0xcb089b8ae76b5df461d40e957603f7a59aea9e0d?a=0x02f08670c84783473521850f37c3544c802b75c8  (you just need the part AFTER token/  Starting from  0x.....  2. then ADD the token Ticker name for Arround which is = ARR  (Token Name)  3. Decimal places = 18.  All set.   YOur MEW DEPOSIT Address is the one main address you see at the top left of screen.     Copy this address, it is where you will send your tokens to.   ...........  Once you have "Added" ARR token to MEW then  4.  LOG INTO Arround ICO website. 5. Click Cabinet.   Then you will see a section to Enter Address. PASTE your MEW address here  (DOUBLE CHECK its 100% Correct!!!)   6. You will then have to log into your email, you signed up with for ICO and confirm the withdrawl.   I think there are two emails. So one to confirm address and one to confirm withdrawl.  7. about 30mins or so later you will see ARR balance in your MEW.

With this in mind, investing in the leaders in the AR field is now considered extremely promising, and funds are being invested from the crypto-community, IT companies as well as companies from the real sector of the economy.   ARROUND.io has proved that even in a falling market, investors are still interested in exciting projects. As the token sale draws to a close, the project has already collected more than 25,000,000 dollars! Of this, 2,000,000 dollars was invested in the project by Asian-Investments, an investment fund operating in the Asia-Pacific region; another 4,000,000 was contributed to ARROUND.io by retail investors, as part of the ongoing ICO project, with RODERY GOLD, one of the world‚Äôs largest gold traders, investing $19,000,000 into the project.  The term Augmented Reality (AR) was originally coined by researcher Tom Codel in1990. The name speaks for itself ‚Äì these are technologies that enhance reality with virtual elements. That is, you pick up your smartphone or tablet, launch the camera and see not just what‚Äôs in front of you in the real world, but also additional elements! For example, King Kong, sitting on top of a skyscraper drinking a Coke, or a Pok√©mon hiding behind a car, or maybe a truck parked right on a square in the center of the city...Augmented reality is a unique technology that allows you to add virtual objects, sounds, and images to the real world. In addition, it‚Äôs also interactive ‚Äì you can influence and play with the virtual objects, take photos with them to post on Instagram and much more!!!  This is the principle behind the ARROUND mobile app, an MVP that‚Äôs already available for download at the App Store and Google Play. The creators of ARROUND.io are applying the technology of augmented reality to advertising, as AR is the single most powerful tool for creating a ‚ÄúWOW effect.‚Äù ARROUND has already launched a campaign for the Scania brand under the slogan ‚ÄúLook ARround.‚Äù ARROUND.io, has ‚Äúparked‚Äù virtual Scania trucks in central locations around the world: in Beijing, Prague, Moscow, Washington, Ottawa, Berlin and other cities ... The company is also developing advertising campaigns with a number of other global business giants:  ‚Ä¢   Unilever ‚Äì the world leader in the market of food and household goods. ‚Ä¢   Carmex ‚Äì the world's number one lip balm. ‚Ä¢   Magnum ‚Äì one of the most popular ice-cream brands in the world. ‚Ä¢   TRESemm√© ‚Äì the world leader in hair care products, founded in the USA in 1947. ‚Ä¢   Campari ‚Äì the Italian producer of market-leading wines, alcoholic and non-alcoholic beverages.   Today, AR is being heavily invested in by Apple, Google, HTC, and Facebook, as well as by private and institutional investors around the world. Everyone still has the opportunity to become an investor in ARROUND ‚Äì the project‚Äôs ICO will continue until November 15, 2018 on the https://arround.io website. The price of one token right now is $0.035, and 3,000,000,000 ARR tokens are available during the sale.

Author: Rasmus_hunter
Title: ARROUND: breakthrough advertising and communication platform in AR
Body: Mobile advertising has rapidly become the most popular channel for digital advertising budgets. Digital mobile spending has now surpassed TV ad spending, making it the single largest destination for adverting dollars in the world, and the trend is expected to continue.  But with the high level of competition and huge supply of commercial offerings, users have become weary of traditional advertising leading to the general consensus that new ideas are needed to engage the public effectively.  AR provides a new and authentic way of engaging with people and spreading campaign messages, be they commercial or social. Campaign images, animations and information are now free to leave the confined surroundings of an Internet page, and literally take form in the real world. Through the freely available technology now embedded in the vast majority of the world‚Äôs smartphones, augmented reality represents the next huge opportunity for marketing and campaign managers.

Author: Crypto_Bro
Title: ARROUND: breakthrough advertising and communication platform in AR
Body: The AR Map links directly to the social network and to the advertising solution. Users of AR Social can take part in a project to map their location simply by scanning the area around them with their smartphone camera. The requirement is only that they have a front facing camera in order to capture a set of data points that will be generated. The technology is similar in nature to 3D scanning, a field which already has a well-developed and widespread set of algorithms that can provide the accuracy required to delivery an immersive AR experience. The resulting data set is a 3D point cloud, tagged to a physical location determined by the GPS, and by additional information such as check-in status and locations known to us.

Author: Ivan_M
Title: ARROUND: breakthrough advertising and communication platform in AR
Body: The AR Store will allow users to conduct the sale and lease transactions of content and services offered on the platform. Content authors will set the prices for their products themselves. It can be free distribution, a freemium model or a one-time/regular payment. Also, there are options for auctions, crowdfunding campaigns and donations.  Third party developers access the store via a development suite, allowing them to test not only software but also test how their hardware interfaces onto the network. Through a powerful SDK and API, ARROUND will be open to all parties who wish to develop the network.  All transactions within the AR Store are priced in fiat, but are undertaken in ARR. When a developer creates an account in the AR Store, they will also be provided with a wallet in which to receive their tokens. Tokens can be freely transferable at an exchange after the Main Token Sale.  The AR Store provides developers access to: ‚Ä¢ SDK ‚Äì a ready-made software solution that will accelerate the development of AR content. ‚Ä¢ API ‚Äì a set of ready-made parameters provided by the application to be implemented in external software products, which will allow third-party developers to integrate their applications into our system and monetize them. ‚Ä¢ The distributed storage where the platform‚Äôs content will be stored. ‚Ä¢ Emulator ‚Äì a section where developers can test their content for compatibility with various types of devices.

Title: ARROUND: breakthrough advertising and communication platform in AR
Body: Since the advent of the Internet, digital and mobile marketing have been the driving force of e-commerce, and there is now an abundance of technology available for even the smallest online retailer to take advantage of. However, in the race to provide ever more effective online advertising and marketing methods, offline retailers have been largely ignored, forced either into a hybrid model of offline/online sales or to offer untargeted discounts and offers via 3rd party sites online in the hope that the customer will remember to visit their shops the next time they are on the high street or in a shopping mall.

Author: Rasmus_hunter
Title: ARROUND: breakthrough advertising and communication platform in AR
Body: ARROUND is fully adopting the emerging technology of augmented reality to provide a decentralized advertising solution for offline retailers that allows them to engage potential customers in the process of shopping, through geo- and socio-targeted push notifications and in-store augmented reality shopping assistance which can even generate discounts for clients while they areselecting products to buy.  Through the activation of the AR Camera within the ARROUND application, consumers will be able to point at specific products or objects in order to activate an AR experience. The AR Camera can be trained to learn visual data in the form of packaging and logos so that when the camera recognizes an item, it can provide additional information about it.  ARROUND can also recognize markers in the form of AR Codes (an analogue of QR codes) to trigger an AR experience for the user. While QR codes provide a uniform experience for all users, AR codes on ARROUND can offer a targeted experience for each individual user, based on their socio-demographic data and the amount of personal information that they have chosen to share on the platform. In this way, ARROUND gives offline retailers access to the same powerful tools that online retailers have enjoyed for years. ARROUND will be an aggregator of AR experiences, so that retailers no longer have to invest in their own application in order to provide an enhanced experience for their customers and supporters.  In addition to tapping this vast reserve of unrealized advertising, ARROUND also provides a unique platform for its users to communicate with each, create content and experience the world around them through the lens of augmented reality. Both the advertisers and users are supported by 3rd party developers who can leverage the powerful SDK and API to create new features, designs and experiences for everyone on the platform via a marketplace.

Author: ARround Team
Title: ARROUND: breakthrough advertising and communication platform in AR
Body: Why own ARR‚ùì  üîπThe ARR is the fundamental unit of exchange within the ARROUND platform, and all commercial activities, although they may be priced in fiat currency, will be conducted in ARR tokens.  üîπARR tokens are used by the platform‚Äôs users to purchase or lease digital items or services from connected developers and by commercial parties in order to run advertising and marketing campaigns. Additionally, tokens can be used to motivate users to view advertising and marketing campaigns, plus provide an incentive for users to map their environment, therefore contributing to the creation of an augmented reality backbone network. Usage of the backbone can be provided to third parties through payment in ARR tokens.

Title: ARROUND: breakthrough advertising and communication platform in AR

ARROUND has a strong supporting cast of partners, including #Scania #Unilever #Campari #HorseForce #Carmex #MoscowZoo among others.  ARROUND creates new opportunities for audience engagement, promotion and marketing using AR technology.

Title: ARROUND: breakthrough advertising and communication platform in AR
Body: üîπHow ARROUND Uses Blockchainüîπ  Blockchain ties all elements of the project together. Advertising inventory and campaigns are registered in the blockchain and paid for by ARR.  A bounty in ARR is paid to map builders and all transactions across the social network are conducted in the ARR token. All intellectual property and privacy rights are guaranteed via smart contracts.

Author: ARround Team
Title: ARROUND: breakthrough advertising and communication platform in AR
Body: What problems does Arround solve‚ùì  üîπThe public is hungry for AR content The public expects and demands ever more engaging augmented reality content. ARROUND offers a disruptive and fully functional AR social platform available for iOS and Android, which will also be ported to consumer smartglasses.  üîπThe mobile marketing channel is saturated Demand for mobile advertising is growing, but the public is tired of traditional approaches. ARROUND offers a new and engaging way for advertisers, brands and organizations to reach their audience in a way that both delights them and informs them.  üîπAR developers have little opportunity to reach the consumer market A growing army of AR developers need a marketplace for their products & services. The use of blockchain ensures IP rights and the AR Store provides a staging area to test new products and services, which ultimate contributes to the development of the social network.

Author: ARround Team
Title: ARROUND: breakthrough advertising and communication platform in AR
Body: ARROUND hits its Soft Cap in just 12 minutes!  The ICO of ARROUND only started on September 15, but the project has already raised $5,000,000 in contributions, covering the Soft Cap in the process. Asian-Investments, a crypto-fund operating in the Pacific-Asian region, invested $2,000,000 in the project.  "We are pleased to announce that ARROUND has reached its first financial milestone of reaching the Soft Cap of our ICO! The cooperation with Asian-Investments is a landmark event for us and we intend to direct the funds raised towards the project and we want to continue moving on our roadmap in the near future", said the CEO of ARROUND Neil Bryant.  Asian-Investments Fund invests mainly in startups that develop solutions in the field of information technology, biotechnology and medicine. ARROUND was one of the first projects in the field of augmented reality to catch the interest of the fund‚Äôs representatives.  ARROUND is developing a decentralized advertising network and platform in augmented reality. According to the original idea of the founders, ARROUND will provide a wide variety of solutions for app users, bloggers, advertisers, advertising agencies, software developers, manufacturers and suppliers of AR-devices. The platform offers a clear value proposition to each participant while saving time and financial resources on customer marketing. Large international companies have already shown interest in the project, including Danone, Unilever, Magnat, TRESemme, Scania and Campari amongst others. ARROUND is currently developing and implementing advertising projects with these household names to run large-scale campaigns.  The appeal of ARROUND to potential customers and partners helped the company to attract investment from Asian-Investments, serving to demonstrate the demand for the solutions offered by the project and for the ARR tokens that are currently on sale at the around.io website.  Asian-Investments Fund specializes in long-term investments and will focus on projects that offer innovative solutions across various areas of the economy. The fund aims to improve the efficiency of capital in emerging Asian markets and promote digital projects and their expansion to new regions. Learn more about the fund at http://asian-investments.com/ and about ARROUND at https://arround.io/  https://www.interfax.ru/pressreleases/630153

Title: ARROUND: breakthrough advertising and communication platform in AR
Body: VIRTUAL Reality (VR) and Augmented Reality (AR) have been buzzwords for quite some time. The idea that one can strap on a VR headset and totally immerse himself in a virtual world, makes great headlines and appeals to tech fans and gamers everywhere.  Augmented Reality is quite a different proposition. While VR has dominated the news, AR is quietly breaking new ground in the enterprise sector. Where VR lets users escape into a totally different reality, AR overlays digital imagery onto the reality people are experiencing. When used with wearable technology such as smart glasses, this blending of digital information with the physical world allows hands-free operation in such environments as healthcare, logistics, maintenance and construction, where the ability to devote both hands to the specific task is critical.  https://medium.com/@arroundsmm/smart-glasses-the-future-of-augmented-reality-eb45c2a4c199  http://a.radikal.ru/a11/1808/3a/ff123684f20d.jpg

Body: Is Augmented Reality the future of Health Care and Pharma industry?  Augmented Reality is an integration of digital information wherein the user is introduced to a real-time environment, it is closer to the real world. The term AR refers to adding graphics, sound effects, images, text, touch feedback etc to create an enhanced user experience. For instance, L‚ÄôOreal‚Äôs Makeup Genius app, allows their users to experience makeup being applied in real time with the help of facial recognition and lighting technology. Next is Timberland‚Äôs AR window-shopping experience which allows passerby to visualise themselves in those clothes without entering the store and trying. AR also has great potential in impacting people‚Äôs lives through pharma and healthcare. According to a report, 91% of people with chronic diseases need managing those diseases between doctor‚Äôs appointment. With the advancement in technologies like AR and low-cost computing, pharma companies and healthcare providers can leverage interactive marketing methods in order to reach the patients in the hour of need. Below mentioned are three ways in which AR marketing can enhance the patient experience.  https://medium.com/@arroundsmm/is-augmented-reality-the-future-of-health-care-and-pharma-industry-f2159cd28191  http://c.radikal.ru/c14/1808/7b/a31ec0f4cb25.png

Author: ARround Team
Title: ARROUND: breakthrough advertising and communication platform in AR
Body: Advertisers have a number of options, which will all be available through a dedicated online portal. They can create and manage banner campaigns, upload 3D objects into the ARROUND universe, create specific actions triggered by images or markers that the AR Camera will detect and retailers can even create a fully fledged navigation experience to an in-store item. In addition, they can add a sponsored AR experience to the AR Store for users on the social network to interact with.  Advertisers will get data on the best locations to run their campaigns and get access to a full suite of blockchain based reporting tools that provide 100% transparency.  Ad prices will be set depending upon the type of campaign being created, but will be in line with existing AR mobile prices.  Users can be motivated to receive targeted advertising via blockchain-based incentives in the form of ARR tokens.  Interactions with adverts or campaigns will be captured automatically (views, engagements, click-through rates, shares etc) and appear in the ad portal.  As for friction, we will optimize the network to limit the number of commercial messages per location, and only target users via permission-based marketing, with those permissions written into the blockchain.

Body: Hi,  If you consider how much of Google and Apple‚Äôs resources are being put into enabling their devices to run AR, then you‚Äôve got an idea of how seriously to take it. Also, AR in itself doesn‚Äôt have to be resource hungry. It uses GPS but if the user isn‚Äôt moving around (like in a car), then that GPS doesn‚Äôt always have to be on for example. There are some great opportunities in AR that we think we can take advantage of, such as building the AR backbone map ‚Äì collecting all the physical data points of the real world that we can use to build the AR experience (Google maps isn‚Äôt accurate enough by the way, plus it doesn‚Äôt map interiors) and giving the people who mine this data a stake in it via the blockchain. If we add a unique social experience and a way to give offline retailers the same kind of advertising tools that e-commerce retailers have had for years (we‚Äôve already got our first agreement to roll this out to nearly 2,000 locations) then we think we‚Äôre onto a winner.  As for using handheld devices rather than smart glasses‚Ä¶our experience presenting ARROUND in various parts of the world shows us that people are already happy to use their handheld devices for AR, but yes, when smart glass appear late this year, or early next year, we‚Äôll already be ready with a social network, ad network and AR map‚Ä¶not a bad place to be.

Body: Augmented reality (AR) is a technology that allows you to change the real world with new information using digital technologies  Augmented reality has already firmly entered the lives of many people. If not to count computer technology and gadgets, it is worth noting that AR is widely used today in medicine, in filmmaking, marketing, and even for military purposes. However, the AR market is not developing so quickly and the main problem faced by users is the lack of interesting content, while low demand from users, in turn, does not create incentives for developers. And here appears ARROUND.  ARROUND project makes augmented reality even more interesting, brighter and more accessible ‚Äì it is an advertising network and communication platform that includes elements of augmented reality. ARROUND allows you to place such items (called "rounds") in specific locations, marking them with geotags, and privacy settings allow users to control who can view their messages. In turn, looking for the next "rounds" you can find new services or entertainment. Just imagine what opportunities this platform opens to you!  ARROUND for users is a platform for communication and entertainment in augmented reality. The infrastructure of the platform with the register in the blockchain is intended for the development and sales of services, advertising, information, goods on the basis of decentralized crypto economy.  ARROUND for advertisers is an innovative affiliate network and a new channel of mobile advertising with unique characteristics. ARROUND platform will be filled with content by users, advertisers, and by robots, transferring especially popular content with geo-tags from open sources (for example, information marked with likes from maps, social networks, portals).  ARROUND for developers - the use of blockchain technology will provide equal conditions and additional guarantees to protect the property rights of owners of digital assets on ARROUND platform, the copyrights of developers and artists living in any country of the world for the AR content created by them. Title: ARROUND: breakthrough advertising and communication platform in AR
Body: How it works for the User  The ARROUND platform represents a combination of virtual and real worlds with a WOW-effect. How does it work? We have two mechanisms for aligning the user and objects in augmented reality with the real-world objects: geopositioning and marker technology.   For the user, the system is convenient and easy to use. It doesn‚Äôt require any special skills or sophisticated hardware except the AR headset or a smartphone that supports AR technology.  The user can open the ARROUND app and see the ARROUND world through her headset lens or mobile phone screen. By pointing the camera at real-world objects, the user can see ‚Äúrounds‚Äù ‚Äî posts in augmented reality made by the user herself or by other users, as well as other content existing in the system. For example, it could be a virtual girl who shows the user around a mall, or it could also be a game (like the world-famous Pok√©mon Go).  By default, rounds (posts) will be deleted 24 hours after being posted to avoid cluttering the space. If the user wants their round to live longer, they can pay for an extension. In order to do that ‚Äî as well as when purchasing other AR content in the system ‚Äî the user can top up their wallet in the system 19 with ARR tokens. All the transactions on the platform will be carried out using ARR tokens. Therefore, the user can buy tokens during the ICO (or on cryptocurrency exchanges after the ICO) and use them in the application by indicating her public cryptocurrency account.  From now on, social media communication is not limited to Facebook. The whole planet becomes your social media landscape, and you can make posts anywhere in the world!  PreSale is live! Title: ARROUND: breakthrough advertising and communication platform in AR
Body: ARROUND: Capital And Expenditure  A successful business venture is one that runs on a concrete plan on how to raise and allocate its capital. For that, ARROUND sits pretty with a very effective and workable solution.  How ARROUND Is Raising Capital  First off, it‚Äôs worth remembering that ARROUND‚Äôs business concept revolves around the main operating token, the ARR. This, of course, is the ultimate currency for all transactions carried out on the platform ‚Äì except at the initial exchange point where the users buy the tokens with fiat currencies from the exchange.  ARROUND is accepting contributions towards the development of the project in two token sales. The total number of tokens is 3 billion, with about 1.69 billion of them meant for public purchase.  ‚Ä¢   The Pre-Sale: This takes just before the main token sale kicks off, with 45 million tokens floated and targeting $1 million worth of sales.  ‚Ä¢   The Main Token Sale: Now, this is the ‚Äúmother of all sales‚Äù by ARROUND. The remaining tokens will be available for people to buy, with the capital in-flow estimated at $50 million with a soft cap of $5 million.   How Will This Money Be Spent?  For a huge venture like ARROUND to really thrive, there needs to be a plan on how best to spend the capital gained, and that‚Äôs exactly what ARROUND is doing. The lions share of the spending will go towards product development (34%) and marketing (31%) to ensure the growth of the platform and cement its status as a market leading advertising solution for offline retailers. Staffing, admin and operational expenses take up the remaining funds raised.  Pre-sale Results So Far  So far, the Pre-sale has raised over $720,000, but there is still a small window available to contributors who wish to receive a 50% bonus on their token purchases. The Pre-sale officially closes on May 1, 2018. But thanks to incredible technologies like blockchain and augmented reality (AR), disruptive service providers such as ARROUND are able to offer something completely new. This new system offers features and a business model even beyond the scope of Virtual Reality.  The ARROUND platform is ready to sweep across the international market and blur the boundaries between online and offline advertising while offering an epic social platform for users that will change how they communicate with the multitude of people around them.  ARROUND for Entertainment and Retail Business  ARROUND can be integrated into other already existing systems like big screens for entertainment and retail business purposes. For example, if a user attends a football match at a stadium, through the use of AR, ARROUND allows them to take selfies with the team mascots, get real-time updates on what‚Äôs happening within the stadium, initiate or join the discussion about the game based on ARROUND‚Äôs inbuilt geo-location features and much more. Advertisers can also serve targeted ads based on the specific user they are trying to attract! ARROUND‚Äôs revolutionary feature-set completely changes the experience of going to a stadium.  In retail business, the system can be employed in shop signs and shop windows to attract customers, present offers, and provide relevant notifications directly into the user‚Äôs newsfeed. Users can then use the fun AR navigation function to find the shops and grab the offers they are interested in.  Content-Driven Adverts  Great advertisers employ very creative ways of capturing a user‚Äôs attention. The ARROUND platform provides unparalleled opportunities for creative agencies to deliver a world-class experience and utilize the latest technology and techniques in their content-driven advertisements.  Advertisers and promoters can create animated graphics, cool designs and other cutting edge visual material to grow their audience with ARROUND. Creating and managing an ad campaign on ARROUND is simple, and is controlled from a special advertiser portal available online. What‚Äôs more, 3rd party developers can offer original content and templates to advertisers to make the process even easier and more effective. ARROUND is an ecosystem built on blockchain, ensuring that transparency is at the core of every transaction on the platform.  ARROUND For Revamping Shopping Malls  Perhaps one of the most notable applications of the new AR concept is the upgrade of business enterprises within their own premises. Malls will find it greatly beneficial to employ this new technology in improving their business operations as well as foster perfection in customer service. For example, the Atrium, which is one of the busiest and largest shopping malls in Russia, is set to test and deploy the new AR technology developed by ARROUND. But how exactly will this technology function within the mall?  ‚Ä¢   Viewing ‚Äúrounds‚Äù: ARROUND presents AR visual impressions known as ‚Äúrounds.‚Äù When a user steps into a mall like the Atrium that runs their advertisements on the ARROUND platform, they can spot these rounds immediately. These may be in form of product adverts and shop signs especially in a mall with various shop outlets under one roof. Also, they may be special offers and other business-related announcements from the shops.  ‚Ä¢   Navigation: Imagine you‚Äôve entered into a large mall and spotted some ‚Äúrounds‚Äù that you‚Äôre really interested in. Your next obvious move would be to start looking for the particular shops where those offers are. The navigation function built into ARROUND will help you with that. Because the rounds are geo-tagged, the system can easily direct you to the exact location. Imagine being guided around a large mall by your favorite virtual character? It‚Äôs not only incredibly useful and timesaving ‚Äì it‚Äôs actually a lot of fun!  ‚Ä¢   Improved user-experience: One sure thing about users of any product or service is that they always tend to come back if they like the experience. A big shopping mall like the Atrium wants to capitalize on this fact to ensure that their clients get the best user-experience within their premises. For that to happen, the mall recognizes the need to employ the best technology available, and that‚Äôs exactly what it is doing. The benefit brought about by the application of ARROUND in shopping malls is expected to expand those markets and ultimately improve their standing in the sector, leading to more clients, which means happier tenants!   Now you see how ARROUND turns the whole business world into a small village! Body: How Exactly Can Retailers Benefit From Using ARROUND?  One of the amazing things about technology is how it can lead to improvements to our day-to-day lives, and augmented reality is one such breakthrough that is currently taking the world by storm. ARROUND is an exciting new platform that provides a brand new AR experience for users, and a complete solution for advertisers who wish to reach them at the point of sale.  ARROUND For Retailers  Imagine a scenario where a customer steps into a shop and immediately spots everything they love showing up right on their app. That‚Äôs what ARROUND‚Äôs new system accomplishes. It means that retail shops can now reach people at the point of sale, harnessing the power of personalization. For example, young mothers may get an offer to buy diapers with a discount, while older men will get vitamin ads. Retailers get a new ability to offer their customers exactly what they need and alert them to the special offers in the shop.  The customer saves time, the retailer knows that it is providing valuable information that improves the overall shopping experience, leading to higher sales receipts and happy shoppers. Just like running an advertising campaign online, the retailer gets access to a special portal where they can mix and match their offers using social and demographic data made available to them. Data is fed to the portal in real time, and the retailer can monitor and adjust the campaign as required to optimize their sales and inventory.  How Businesses Can Win by Using ARROUND  The fact that ARROUND is based on a new technology isn‚Äôt really its most important feature. It‚Äôs the operational concept behind it that makes people stop and pay attention. ARROUND is modeled around the need to solve problems, and in this case break down the barriers between retailers and their customer base. It provides a clear solution to the problem of reaching consumers close to the point of sale, when they are most likely to make a purchase.  Reach Customers: Through the platform, users can find and select special offers right away, exactly when they need them. Any retailer can impress their customers with personalized offers, in some ways it‚Äôs like VIP advertising. Customers feel the connection and keep shopping at the outlet in the future.  Create the Perfect Adverts: It‚Äôs a fact that a business that excels in presenting its products and services is a successful business. ARROUND provides a platform for businesses to create engaging animated presentations of their products and services, making sure that the user gets exactly what they need. This functionality embraces the concept of customization to present personalized offers and adverts to target potential and current customers or a group of users.  Foster Good Business-Customer Relations: Since shoppers can find what they want easily on the AR platform, they don‚Äôt need to go store-hopping looking for a particular product or service. This deepens the connection between businesses and their customer base and ultimately fosters an atmosphere of trust, credibility, and reliability. Exactly what every business needs.  Advanced platforms such as ARROUND are set to revolutionize the global business of mobile advertising. All a user needs is the app on their smartphone, nothing could be easier. Body: ARROUND's Roadmap to Disrupt Mobile Advertising Using Augmented Reality  While the field of augmented reality has had various players in the past and there are currently a number of companies working in the space, the entry of ARROUND into the market represents a fundamental shift in how augmented reality can be commercialized. ARROUND is storming the AR market with a clear objective to present a solution that is more original and more efficient than anything so far available. ARROUND provides a disruptive advertising solution for retailers using augmented reality, which brings the power of the Internet closer to the point of sale.  To support its goals, ARROUND has a defined a roadmap for its growth and commercialization. When the idea of ARROUND was first conceived in 2016, the company discussed the potential of AR with the business community and the feedback received was integral in developing the business concept behind the new communication and advertising network based on Augmented Reality.  ARROUND Project Launch  The year 2017 saw ARROUND‚Äôs overall project get launched with an initial private equity investment round and the specification of the platform. ARROUND quickly caught the attention of some major companies like Russia‚Äôs 36.6 who saw the potential and signed on as partners. 36.6 owns the largest pharmacy chain in Russia, but the project doesn‚Äôt stop here. ARROUND to Go Mobile  The ARROUND mobile App is going live in 2018!  In today‚Äôs world, when you really want to get the public‚Äôs attention, you do it through an App. ARROUND understands this, and the platform has been designed to be accessible to anyone with a smartphone. This App is set to kick-start the formal entry of the new AR platform into the global market. To ensure inclusivity, the MVP (the initial product that will be launched by ARROUND) can run on both Android and iOS. It will have the following functionalities:  ‚Ä¢   Camera: With the ARROUND Camera, users can capture rounds or geo-tagged objects that interest them and create rounds for their friends and other ARROUND users. ‚Ä¢   Newsfeed: If a user follows other users, they can receive updates and news about their rounds right in their newsfeed. ‚Ä¢   Map: If you spot an offer or round that you would like to grab, you can use the map to get to the location in question and do just that.  The launch of a buzzing campaign with the backing of major partners like the Atrium mall and 36.6 will usher in the new age of doing business on an integrated AR platform. The alpha release of the functional platform will see its first action and content feeds as ARROUND finally opens its doors to the mass market.  Empowering the User  ARROUND recognizes the importance of developing an open platform that can integrate every up and coming hardware development that can add to the user‚Äôs enjoyment of the service, such as the Microsoft Lens and the ODG Augmented Reality Glasses. The integration of these technologies with the ARROUND platform‚Äôs functionalities would greatly tune up its efficiency and boost the overall user experience.  In fact, in 2019, ARROUND will have advertising agencies fully served on the platform. A good campaign drive targeting the major pharmacy networks in Europe should bring in more users onto the platform. Advertising agencies will get a special module to help them develop their customized adverts and content.  Going Global  By 2020, ARROUND will be in the best possible position to fully take on the secondary market, with the initial auction of advertising space happening the same year. This is also the year that third-party developers get their specialized SDK to properly operate within the platform.  In effect, these developments will see ARROUND expand into big markets like Asia, particularly China, Japan, and Korea, and also further into Europe. Besides that, ARROUND plans to find a good partner and run a scheduled pilot project in the United States. By the time that happens, ARROUND and its token-based ecosystem will be a force to reckon with in the global market. This is how technological revolutions happen.  About ARROUND  ARROUND is disrupting the AR space, harnessing the power of this innovative new technology to provide a service to users, advertisers, and developers simultaneously. ARROUND provides a comprehensive solution for advertisers using augmented reality, based on the blockchain and cryptocurrencies. Title: ARROUND: breakthrough advertising and communication platform in AR
Body: Blockchain On The ARROUND Platform  Using Blockchain on ARROUND  Debuting into the sector as one of the most promising start-ups in the field of Augmented Reality (AR), ARROUND recognizes the need to deploy the latest and most reliable technologies on its platform, and that includes blockchain.  Blockchain: The Background  The blockchain technology is basically a chain-like representation of database records in the form of blocks. These separate blocks are linked together to form a chain. Each block contains a referential cryptographic hash that links it back to the previous block. Since the records are always growing, new blocks are continuously created, forming a large complex system that is decentralized.  And it‚Äôs this complexity and decentralization that makes blockchain technology so valuable since it‚Äôs much less prone to errors and security breaches as opposed to taking a centralized approach. In fact, each transaction is validated across multiple blocks and records, making the whole system appear as distributed yet very closely-knit in its actual operational capacity. The verification of transactions through multiple points of reference makes the blockchain technology immune to fraud and void of glitches, making it the most secure distributed system ever.   From The CTO: The Role Of Block-Chain on the ARROUND Platform  ARROUND‚Äôs Dmitry Livshin, who is the company‚Äôs Chief Technology Officer, believes that the choice of using blockchain brings a number of benefits both to the company and the community of users as a whole. For instance, blockchain technology better protects the property rights for digital assets owned by various users on the platform. It‚Äôs also excellent in enforcing copyright policies to protect artists and developers using the system from anywhere in the world. In fact, blockchain opens up a number of new commercial opportunities on the platform, something that using a conventional payment system makes incredibly complex and requires a great deal of trust between the contracting parties. With blockchain, the trust is built-into the actual system, reducing the need for additional reputation based systems that complicate transactions and lead to internal market price discrepancies.  Since it‚Äôs based on a distributed ledger system, the introduction of blockchain in AR will foster confidence and inspire the participants‚Äô trust in the system as it works to ensure all transactions are transparent, mobile, and reliable. Also, owing to its high-security standards, the technology will greatly help secure the platform‚Äôs internal information and handle processing functions for token balances in transactions initiated by users through EC20 Smart Contracts.  As a bonus, the blockchain system also allows for the division of the ecosystem into specialized platforms for various functions. That‚Äôs much better and more convenient than using a single system for everything. One of these is a special chain dedicated to handling virtual payments like Ethereum as well as managing the circulation of ARR tokens on the system. In fact, being able to use tokens was another key reason for choosing blockchain. All transactions on the platform are conducted in ARR, the internal token of the ARROUND system, a token that will be available for purchase on the leading digital exchanges.  Is ARROUND Prepared for Blockchain?  Now, talking about the blockchain in relation to the platform in use is one thing, and actually being prepared for it to for the core technology around which the entire ecosystem is developed is entirely another. So how is ARROUND prepared for this?  For starters, ARROUND strives to provide the most reliable and secure infrastructure for blockchain to run on. To achieve this, ARROUND is developing all the digital layers of the product with the necessary functionality to support the continuous replication of its running environment in a manner most suitable for blockchain. This will allow a variety of content to be propagated within the ARROUND ecosystem and has the effect of entrenching the idea of the platform‚Äôs reliability among all users including developers, artists, and advertisers.  Understanding the power of the blockchain technology, it‚Äôs no surprise that next-generation technology companies like ARROUND would want to make it the core concept of the ARROUND augmented reality ecosystem. Title: ARROUND: breakthrough advertising and communication platform in AR
Body: What ARROUND  Brings To The Market  Breakthroughs in technology always attract headlines around the world, and in turn inspire the creative potential of the world‚Äôs community of entrepreneurs. Just a few years ago, it wasn‚Äôt even possible to imagine a technology capable of enhancing reality itself actually becoming a mainstream fixture of our daily lives. But a series of innovations in the microchip industry, in battery technology, in Big Data, geospatial positioning, blockchain and a host of others have all combined to bring Augmented Reality out of the movies and into the real world. Life as we know it is about to change, and entities like ARROUND are now working day tirelessly to bring the technology to the mass market.   ARROUND Vs The Competition  As a technological field, Augmented Reality had long been living under the shadow of Virtual Reality, but that has now changed as users and the marketplace understand that AR is about being mobile ‚Äì it‚Äôs about being in the real world and living our normal lives with AR acting as an ever present assistant. In fact, total revenue generated from AR is much higher than that from VR, and the trend is only predicated to continue. As a company firmly in the AR blockchain space, ARROUND  also faces competition from other industry players, but the company‚Äôs unique vision shows some clear advantages over the field.  First, while some players like Spheroid Universe and Arcona use third-party block-chain systems, ARROUND will use a proprietary blockchain, in addition they are creating a precise business model complete with a stakeholder reward system, a customizable marketing and advertising platform with a variety of choices, and partnering with the right entities ‚Äì large retail networks and shopping malls in the first instance. All this accords ARROUND an impressive competitive edge in regard to claiming its stake as an open platform ready to serve the growing needs of users, advertisers and AR developers.  Secondly, the ARROUND platform has some unique built-in communication features, allowing integration with the world‚Äôs leading social networks. This means that advertising and other AR content on the platform has the potential to go viral ‚Äì both within ARROUND and also on the Internet as a whole. ARROUND runs an on-platform economy based on the blockchain that make it easier for all the participants on the platform to share, sell and even lease their content in a transparent and hassle-free way.  Ultimately, while there are countless applications for AR technology, from virtual dinosaur theme parks to museums and galleries, ARROUND has chosen to launch in a very specific field, the area of shopping and advertising. This gives ARROUND a specific competitive advantage in being able to commercialize the product immediately and maximize potential revenues.   Flowing With The Trend  Because technology is always advancing and new ideas are always bubbling to the surface, ARROUND‚Äôs business model takes into account the need to keep abreast of any ground-breaking developments in the AR world as well other issues relevant to the AR industry. ARROUND wants to offer users the best of the AR world, and new enhancements will be integrated into the platform by the global network of developers who are plugged into the ARROUND ecosystem and have the motivation to create new apps.  For this, the ARROUND platform introduces a mobile app, a systemic ecosystem, as well as lots of useful content for users. For example, the ARROUND Camera enables users to easily locate geo-tagged objects of interest like blogs, promo-campaigns and shops. The user has the power to turn their status visibility on or off whenever they like. There‚Äôs also a newsfeed to keep users updated on events and happenings based on their interests. The ARROUND Map provides tips on where to locate new rounds, which also comes with the option to turn location discovery on or off. If your location is on and another user gets interested in your rounds, they can add you to their newsfeed to keep updated about your rounds. Enter ARR token.  The Token  Think of a society. A society can‚Äôt survive without supporting trade among its members, and this trade needs some kind of regulation to ensure that everyone gets the appropriate value for their tradable assets. Since this society is too advanced to reintroduce barter trade, it goes without saying that the regulation should come in the form of a currency. However, there‚Äôs another twist in that this society happens to exist in a virtual world ‚Äì online, to be precise. That means that the currency in question must be transferable by digital means. That‚Äôs the concept that ARR token is based upon.  Since ARROUND accepts users from all around the world and deals solely in digital assets, it has made great efforts to embrace the emerging technologies that are making business easier and more beneficial. In this respect, ARR token has been introduced as the ultimate currency for all ARROUND users.  Tokens On ARROUND Platform  Good news is that you can use tokens to trade digital goods and services on ARROUND  platform, and as the tokens are based on ERC20 smart contracts, all parties involved in any trade can be sure that each and every trade is safe.  The basics of operating within ARROUND platform is to employ its facilities in the propagation of digital content in an effort to boost the trade volume within the ecosystem, and this trade will only happen when users acquire the tokens that are the universal currency in ARROUND world.  In essence, the users convert fiat currencies into ARR tokens, which they can then use to buy digital services and goods on ARROUND platform. The first user of ARROUND platform is the user who buys the tokens at the initial Token Sale, after which any additional tokens are to be bought through the exchange system. With the token pre-sale currently underway, the maximum number of tokens to be circulated is capped at 3 billion, with a single token going for USD 0.035.  Significance Of  ARR Token On The Platform  With ARR being the currency of the platform, all users and advertisers will need to use ARR to transact on ARROUND. ARROUND  runs an ecosystem based explicitly on a token economy. The only time a user transacts using fiat currencies is when buying the tokens at the exchange. All other transactions on the platform are token-based.  One key factor of using tokens is the ability of advertisers to provide incentives to users through token distribution. Advertisers can set tasks to users, for example to share product details, or visit a shop, all tasks which can be rewarded with the ecosystem. This gives ARROUND platform a very interesting feature, it allows advertising campaigns to go viral, not only within the platform, but online too through ARROUND‚Äôs integration with existing social networks.  Through the introduction of a common currency on the platform, the ecosystem stands to gain by normalizing trade as well as boosting transactional integrity. In other words, since all users are using the same currency, and with the added benefit of smart contracts all participants know that trust is no longer an issue. It‚Äôs clear that the buzz caused by  ARR token on  ARROUND  platform is bound to bring about a revolution in how online-based platforms run their business, and ARROUND is ready to be at the forefront of this revolution. Title: ARROUND: breakthrough advertising and communication platform in AR
Body: Introducing ARROUND: The New Augmented Reality Platform Ready to Take on the World  In a changing world where the digital domain is rapidly merging with our real one, the inception of Augmented Reality (AR) technology has been long-overdue. There are a number of startups taking on the tech industry to stake their claim in this exponentially growing market. ARROUND is a platform that helps AR users in ways that only a handful of others have attempted.   Augmented Reality: Market Overview  Augmented Reality is a new kind of technology that‚Äôs rapidly taking root in the global market. With the main delivery channel being through smartphones, this technology boasts a ready market of over 2.3 billion people currently equipped with these communication devices. In fact, the AR industry is projected to be worth a staggering $115 billion by 2020, a hundred-fold increase since the trend was first noticed in 2016, and there are no signs that it‚Äôs going to stop there.  In addition, the number of people with smartphones (where users can already experience Augmented Reality) is due to increase as more people gain access to the internet, especially with the current efforts to make internet access free and accessible from anywhere in the world. This is bound to make AR a heavily contested field as everyone scrambles to get a feel of the new technology. You remember what happened when touch-screen smartphones first hit the market a few years back? Added to this the new developments in wearable AR glasses and it‚Äôs clear to see that the time for AR to hit mainstream adoption is finally here.  Who Are The Players?  People born around 1995 and after are projected to be the core users of this technology going forward, as they‚Äôre currently leading the curve in terms of tech adoption. It‚Äôs therefore safe to opine that AR will be a natural component of day-to-day life of the majority of Generation Z. In turn, and in order to deal with the expected high demand, various leading hardware manufacturing companies like Toshiba, Apple, Asus and Microsoft have already entered the game to develop the tools and associated technologies to better serve the AR experience.  With the growing support for AR technology, it‚Äôs expected that various other entities will entities will invest in the industry, and ARROUND is well positioned to take advantage of this flurry of activity in the new AR industry.   ARROUND Vs The Market  To build its status as a leader in the market, ARROUND employs creativity to ensure efficiency and ease of use of the products offered ‚Äì you don‚Äôt have to know any programming skills to use the platform. Also, being a flexible platform that can be used by a variety of industries, it strives to provide appropriate AR-solutions for many use cases. For example, in the case of advertisers, ARROUND offers 3 packages for use by shopping malls, retail outlets, and large events such as soccer matches.  While still in start-up mode, ARROUND has already taken some major steps towards the mainstream, in particular it has partnered with the 36.6 group, Russia‚Äôs largest pharmacy and cosmetics network, which means it can commercialize it‚Äôs product from day one as well as create additional demand for AR. The company also plans to expand its network into South East Asia, Europe, and North America, growing the size of the network and it‚Äôs associated revenue considerable during this time.  It‚Äôs clear that the AR market is set for explosive growth over the coming years, it‚Äôs spawning an entire industry that is ready to blossom, and anyone with a keen mind who is questioning what the future is going to look like is starting to look to AR for the answer.
